\item[* task:] To turn object and indirect object NPVARs or CNVARs into
preadvrels, when no aanobjrel or voorobjrel is present.
\item[\ \ strategy:] (also: deviations from accepted proposals)

The relation name is lost after application of this transformation.
It might be useful to retain it. This makes sense for the surface parser,
and for making the coice for the objrel or indobjrel more deterministic,
as e.g. in TNPoverADV2.
It can best be done in combination with the argrel strategy for V-raising.

The preadvrel is put as far to the left as possible. A consequence is that
e.g. {\em ..dat hij gisteren de man niet zag} cannot be derived, only
{\em ..dat hij de man gisteren niet zag} can. To achieve the result that
also the first one is generated, as one of the options, a separate hopping
transformation is necessary. This does not exist yet.

Deeply emdedded VARs can (in combination with VR and pruning) 
get higher by this rule, e.g. {\em dat hij die man niet wil zien}. In
English deep, (over unlimited distances) substitution is necesary 
in such cases. This problem has not been solved yet.

